name: PEACE FOR ALL Graphic T-Shirt | Artemis - E481930-000
description: PEACE FOR ALL“It’s time for action, in the name of world peace.” Major figures who share this vision with UNIQLO have volunteered to design Tshirts expressing their peaceful wishes. All proceeds will be donated to international organizations supporting those affected by violence, discrimination, armed conflict, and poverty. The Peace for All project is powered by each and every one of you who wears these Tshirts. Our wish is for a world in which all people can feel the peace of a future where everyone can live safely together. UNIQLO will continue to broaden this initiative, working with people all around the world.*UNIQLO parent company Fast Retailing Co., Ltd. will donate an amount equivalent to all profits (no less than 20% of the selling price) equally among UNHCR, Save the Children Japan, and Plan International Inc. This sales promotion is conducted by Fast Retailing, a parent company of UNIQLO Japan.Club for the FutureNonprofit Organization / Club for the Future is a nonprofit with the mission to inspire and mobilize future generations to pursue careers in STEAM (science, technology, engineering, arts, and math) for the benefit of Earth. The Club and its partners are doing this through the Postcards to Space program, providing spacefocused lessons and events, and activating ambassadors around the world.From Space, Earth has no borders. The profound insights gained from space exploration impacts our perception of our home and humanity. It emphasizes the interconnectedness of all people, regardless of their backgrounds, and the shared responsibility we hold in protecting our planet. The reflections of astronauts Leland Melvin, Sian Proctor, and Gary Lai are depicted in the spacethemed PEACE FOR ALL shirts. They highlight the transformative power of viewing Earth from above, inspiring a sense of unity and hope.The themes of connection, hope, and belonging resonate strongly. By recognizing that Earth is a singular, harmonious entity without borders, we can nurture a collective vision for a peaceful future. This is a powerful reminder of our responsibilities towards each other and the planet.This is not only a wish for peace but also a call to action, encouraging everyone to embrace their role in fostering a brighter future for generations to come.PEACE FOR ALL. SPACE FOR EARTH.Product ID: 481930

description: MANGA curationFeaturing “Berserk,” “Parasyte,” and “Uzumaki,” which have long garnered a large following due to their worldview, stories, and artistry, this is a collection of titles selected by UT from the perspective of graphic Tshirts that bring the profound world of MANGA to life.Born in Chiba, Kentaro Miura. name: MANGA curation UT Graphic T-Shirt | Uzumaki - E479031-000
description: MANGA curationFeaturing “Berserk,” “Parasyte,” and “Uzumaki,” which have long garnered a large following due to their worldview, stories, and artistry, this is a collection of titles selected by UT from the perspective of graphic Tshirts that bring the profound world of MANGA to life.Junji Ito was born on July 31st, 1963 in Nakatsugawa, Gifu Prefecture.After graduating from high school, he entered dental technician school and entered the work force. However, when the ‘Monthly Halloween’ (Asahi Sonorama) newcomer manga award the ‘Umezu Award’ was established, he submitted his work with the singleminded desire to have it read by Kazuo Umezu.In 1986, he received an honorable mention for his contribution ‘Tomie’. This was his debut work and became his bestknown title.Three years later, he quit his job as a dental technician to concentrate on his manga career.In 1998, he began serializing ‘Uzumaki’ in Weekly Big Comic Spirits (Shogakukan).Since then, he has continued to publish oneofakind works.He has won ‘The Will Eisner Comic Industry Award’, one of the world's most prestigious awards for manga artists, four times in total, and in 2023 received the ‘Special Honors Award’ at the Angoulême International Manga Festival in France, as well as the ‘Inkpot Award’ at San Diego ComicCon in the USA.©Junji ITO/ShogakukanProduct ID: 479031

name: Disney in Blue UT Graphic T-Shirt - E480139-000
description: Disney in BlueBUAISOU, an indigo dyer and farmer collective known for blending tradition with modern craftsmanship, has garnered worldwide attention. Inspired by the rich hues of natural indigo, UNIQLO has launched an exclusive collection featuring Mickey Mouse and his friends as its motifs. Enjoy this beautiful lineup of blues crafted from the finest indigo. Note: The products use synthetic dyes inspired by natural indigo.BUAISOUFounded in 2015 and based in Kamiita Town, Tokushima Prefecture, BUAISOU manages the entire indigo dyeing process—from cultivating indigo and producing the dye material, "sukumo," to crafting the final products— traditionally carried out by separate artisans. In addition to creating original indigodyed items and collaborating with others, they also participate in exhibitions and workshops both in Japan and abroad,sharing the beauty of natural indigo through various methods.©DisneyProduct ID: 480139

description: Disney in BlueBUAISOU, an indigo dyer and farmer collective known for blending tradition with modern craftsmanship, has garnered worldwide attention. Enjoy this beautiful lineup of blues crafted from the finest indigo. description: Disney in BlueBUAISOU, an indigo dyer and farmer collective known for blending tradition with modern craftsmanship, has garnered worldwide attention. Inspired by the rich hues of natural indigo, UNIQLO has launched an exclusive collection featuring Mickey Mouse and his friends as its motifs. Enjoy this beautiful lineup of blues crafted from the finest indigo. Note: The products use synthetic dyes inspired by natural indigo.BUAISOUFounded in 2015 and based in Kamiita Town, Tokushima Prefecture, BUAISOU manages the entire indigo dyeing process—from cultivating indigo and producing the dye material, "sukumo," to crafting the final products— traditionally carried out by separate artisans. name: Ai Yazawa Collection UT Graphic T-Shirt - E475530-000
description: A Tshirt designed with inspiration from Tenshi nanka ja nai(I'm No Angel).Ai Yazawa Collection2025 marks the Japanese manga artist Ai Yazawa's 40th anniversary since her debut. Her captivating works have garnered a global following, transcending generations, and the stylish fashion of her characters is one of the highlights. This collection showcases four of her works: Tenshi nanka ja nai(I'm No Angel), Gokinjo Monogatari(Neighborhood Story), Paradise Kiss, and NANA. The designs are inspired by the outfits worn by the characters in these stories, along with original illustrations created specifically for this collection.Ai YazawaBorn in Hyogo Prefecture, Ai Yazawa made her debut in 1985 with Ano Natsu(That Summer) in the Ribon Original early spring issue.
